details.description:
The Jordan 5 Retro Grape 2025 edition revives a colorway that helped redefine sneaker culture far beyond the hardwood. Originally launched in 1990, the "grape ice" and "new emerald" palette broke the mold, a bold move at the time for a Jordan model. What set it apart wasn’t what happened on the court, but what happened on screen and in the streets. Think Will Smith rocking them lace-free in The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air and MJ flashing them on a Wheaties box. That energy is back, this time with the OG Nike Air heel branding and shape to match.

This version of the "Grapes" get it right. Clean white leather uppers, the classic tongue, and icy translucent soles return, now crafted with more attention to the original than we’ve seen in decades. Tinker Hatfield’s fighter jet–inspired details are sharper than ever, and the silhouette has been fine-tuned to mirror the 1990 blueprint. Whether you’re a longtime collector or just building your rotation, this pair hits the perfect balance of nostalgia and current heat.

eReleased on June 21, 2025, the Jordan 5 Retro Grape (2025) dropped at a retail price of $210. Featuring a fresh blend of white, grape ice, and new emerald, this reissue pays homage to the cultural wave that made the 5s iconic.

name: Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined

details.description:
The Air Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined pays homage to one of Jordan Brand’s most iconic designs, first debuted in 1990. This updated version reimagines the timeless sneaker with subtle yet impactful modern tweaks, staying true to its legendary roots. Featuring a sleek black nubuck upper, reflective metallic silver tongues, and bold fire red accents on the Jumpman logo, this sneaker effortlessly blends heritage with innovation.

Every detail has been carefully crafted to elevate its legacy. The 3M reflective tongue and metallic silver shark teeth on the midsole add depth and dimension, while translucent netting and a visible Air unit in the heel enhance both style and comfort. Beloved touches like the "Nike Air" branding on the heel and upside-down "Air Jordan" text inside the tongue provide nostalgic nods to the original design while keeping the sneaker relevant.

Released on February 8, 2025,the Air Jordan 5 Black Metallic Reimagined retailed for $210. This version marks the 35th anniversary of the silhouette and is part of Jordan Brand’s highly anticipated Reimagined lineup, giving both longtime fans and newcomers a fresh reason to celebrate.

name: Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (GS)

details.description:
The Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (GS) brings one of Jordan Brand’s most legendary sneakers to a new generation of sneakerheads. Originally debuting in 1990, the Black Metallic colorway is a staple in the Air Jordan lineup, and this Reimagined edition stays true to its heritage while adding subtle modern refinements. Built for kids who want to step into sneaker history, this GS version features a sleek black nubuck upper, a reflective metallic silver tongue, and bold fire red Jumpman branding, delivering the same iconic look in a size made for smaller feet.

Designed with both style and comfort in mind, this pair includes metallic silver shark teeth on the midsole, translucent netting, and a visible Air unit in the heel—elements that have defined the AJ5 for over three decades. The 3M reflective tongue catches the light with every step, while nostalgic details like the Nike Air branding on the heel and the upside-down Air Jordan text on the tongue pay tribute to the OG design. Whether rocking them on the playground or the pavement, these kicks bring a piece of sneaker history to a new audience.

Released on March 2, 2025, for a retail price of $160, the Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (GS) continues the legacy of one of the most celebrated Air Jordan 5 colorways. As part of Jordan Brand’s 35th anniversary Reimagined lineup, this kids’ version ensures the next generation can lace up a true classic.

name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Quai 54 Black Tour Yellow Red

details.description:
If you're looking for a striking-looking trainer with top-class credentials, the Jordan 5 Retro Reverse Metallic is right up there. It's an almost surrealistic take on the traditional high-top basketball shoe, with ultra-modern contours and high-tech accents.

This is a fascinating update on the Air Jordan 5. It has an ice white upper punctuated with black panels on the sole and collar. The leather upper has a synthetic mesh cut-out panel for breathability. The collar has a high front, crested by a long tongue, and an ultra-low back. The midsole has jagged white highlighting that creates a dramatic effect.

Our experts are very taken by this design. It's aggressive but also very familiar at the same time. It screams aggressive hoop action and makes one want to get out and play. The transparent air capsule in the heel adds the perfect high-performance touch. The Jordan 5 Retro Reverse Metallic was released on 7 December 2024, priced at $200 retail.

Michael Jordan is paying homage to his alma mater, The University of North Carolina, with the release of the Air Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue.

The Jordan 5 UNC comes in the Tar Heels signature University Blue across the uppers and is dressed with University Blue laces, and lace locks. A black midsole with white and University Blue detailing separates the translucent blue outsole from the suede uppers. The sneakers are topped off with a silver reflective 3M tongue with a black jumpman logo.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue released March 5, 2023, with a retail price of $225.

name: Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (PS)

details.description:
The Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (PS) is a shoe for preschoolers with a sleek, dark design.

This version of the Jordan 5 Retro OG comes with an upper made of calf suede in black. The upper is layered, with separate panels for the toe box, toe cap, side panels, ankle, and heel. The sides of the shoe are void of suede to reveal metallic grey mesh for breathability. The tongue is also a metallic silver color with a red Jumpman logo. The Nike Air logo also appears on the heel in silver. The shoe features a black midsole with a splash of silver speckled with black.

Our favorite thing about this shoe is the grey mesh that peeks out from underneath the suede on the sides, giving this shoe a pop of lightness against the black build. The Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (PS) was released on February 8, 2025, for $90.

name: Jordan 5 Retro A Ma Maniére Dawn (Women's)

details.description:
Step into the dawn of a new era with the exclusive A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 5 "Dawn". This collaboration infuses classic elegance with a street-ready edge. The leather upper pairs with a gleaming metallic silver tongue, preserving the silhouette's celebrated features like the prominent "23" on the heel and the distinctive shark teeth design. ​
​​
​Echoing the hues of early morning skies, the "Dawn" presents a color palette of Photon Dust, Black, Diffused Blue, and Pale Ivory. It's an all-new colorway, a testament to A Ma Maniére's finesse and Jordan's timeless appeal. The slimmed-down collar and pre-yellowed quarter panel netting, round out the exclusive design elements.​
​​
​Released on November 17, 2023, and priced at $225, this women's exclusive sneaker is a must-have for collectors and style mavens alike. Grab your pair and witness the rise of a new icon.

The Jordan 5 Retro SE Sail is a special edition of the iconic high-top men’s basketball shoe that comes in a Sail and black colorway.

This version of the Jordan 5 Retro SE is made with premium material, including leather and textile cushioning. The upper of the shoe comes in a Sail beige color, which adorns the base and the overlays. On each side of the shoe under the laces there is a small window showcasing the white mesh cushion. Black detailing adorns the white rubber outsole under the forefoot, and there’s a visible Air unit in the heel. The Jumpman logo appears in black on the heel and on the tongue. The tongue is made of flat canvas for more flexibility of movement.

What we like best about this shoe is the black shark tooth design under the forefoot. This adds a pop of visual appeal to the otherwise simple shoe. The Jordan 5 Retro SE Sail was released on April 13, 2024, for a retail price of $210.

name: Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss

details.description:
The Air Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss is a collaboration between footwear brand and the American musician.

This Retro Air Jordan 5 comes in crimson bliss , leche blue-sail colorway. The upper is coral leather with a Leche Blue quilted lining. Each heel overlay has the Nike Air logo on the right and 'We the Best' on the left. Reflective silver tongues feature Jumpman branding. Off-white polyurethane midsole with blue shark-tooth detailing and Air-sole unit in heel. Mismatched Jumpman and 'We the Best' branding appear on the outsoles.

The Air Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss was released on the 28th of November 2022, retailing for $225.

name: Jordan 5 Retro Fire Red Silver Tongue (2020)

details.description:
Jordan remastered a 1990s masterpiece with the release of the Jordan 5 Retro Fire Red Silver Tongue (2020), now available on StockX. This is the fourth iteration of the original Fire Red colorway.

This Jordan 5 consists of a white leather upper with netted underlays and Fire Red detailing. A silver 3M reflective tongue with a red Jumpman logo, black and Fire Red midsole, and an icy translucent outsole completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $200.

2021 marked 12 years since the Air Jordan 5 Defining Moments pack dropped, and in the same year, one-half of that pack resurfaced on the SNKRS app.

The Air Jordan 5 Raging Bulls is a suede lover’s dream, bringing back the same look and feel from the 2009 version. The upper is composed entirely out of red suede, celebrating MJ’s tenure with the Chicago Bulls. From there, a red and black embroidered "23" appears on the lateral side of each shoe’s heel, highlighting Jordan’s quintessential jersey number. In usual Jordan 5 fashion, the upper part of the tongue is made of reflective materials with a contrasting black Jumpman logo. Lastly, the model’s World War II fighter jet inspiration is made apparent from the white and red shark tooth details that lay atop a black midsole.

The Air Jordan 5 Raging Bulls released in April of 2021 for $190.

The Jordan 5 Retro Golden Ticket (Women's) is a stunning addition to the iconic Air Jordan lineup. This women's exclusive colorway showcases a luxurious blend of Earth, Metallic Gold, Sail, and Muslin hues, creating a sophisticated and eye-catching design. The upper features a premium suede construction in a rich earth tone, complemented by metallic gold accents that add a touch of elegance to the classic silhouette. The signature mesh panels and lace toggles remain true to the original Air Jordan 5 design, while the midsole incorporates the model's distinctive shark tooth detailing.

Comfort and performance are at the forefront of this release, with the Air Jordan 5's renowned cushioning system providing excellent support for all-day wear. The shoe's collar is padded for added comfort, and the tongue features the iconic Jumpman logo. The outsole boasts a combination of solid rubber and translucent sections, offering superior traction and durability. Our experts state this product is great for fashion-forward sneaker enthusiasts who appreciate a perfect blend of style and heritage in their footwear.

Having debuted in 2006, the Air Jordan 5 Green Bean (2022) marks the first time the colorway has ever been reissued. It arrives in its original grey reflective construction with hits of Green Bean on the tongue and midsole. At the base, an icy blue semi translucent outsole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 5 Green Bean (2022) released in May of 2022 and retailed for $210.

The Air Jordan 5 Moonlight arrives looking identical to the original 2013 Jordan 5 Oreo. It features a black Durabuck upper with translucent netted inserts and grey embroidered Jumpman logos on the tongue. From there, a white midsole with black speckled shark teeth and an icy translucent sole brings a contrast to the monotone upper.

The Air Jordan 5 Moonlight released in September of 2021 and retailed for $190.

name: Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (TD)

details.description:
The Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (TD) is a sleek shoe with metallic accents for toddlers.

The Black Metallic Reimagined (TD) Jordan 5 Retro OG mainly has black suede panels stitched together with black thread. The toe box, side panels, toe cap, and heel are different suede layers. The side panels reveal gray mesh with rounded rectangular perforations for increased airflow. The metallic silver tongue contains a red Air Jordan Jumpman logo, while the Nike Air logo appears on the heel in silver thread. The look is complete with a black midsole with silver accents and a light blue outsole.

What stands out about this shoe is the light blue accents of the outsole, which add welcome pops of color to the design. The Jordan 5 Retro OG Black Metallic Reimagined (TD) was released on February 8, 2025, for a retail price of $75.

To honor the 30th Anniversary of the Jordan 5, Jordan Brand added a "What The?" treatment to its catalog with the Jordan 5 What The. This design boasts a mix of materials and details from Jumpman’s best Non-OG Jordan 5 colorways, including the Tokyo, Shanghai, Raging Bull, Bel-Air, Laser, Green Bean, Olive, and Quai 54 colorways.

In true mismatched fashion, each foot of the Jordan 5 What The showcases a different look. On the right, yellow suede from the Tokyo 5 smothers the upper atop a purple and blue speckled Belair 5 midsole with a patterned interior pulled from the Jordan 5 Olive. On the left, red suede tributing the Raging Bull Jordan 5 covers the upper atop a black, grey, and lime green sole that references the Quai 54 iteration. Heel embroidery nodding to the Shanghai and Tokyo models, icy translucent outsoles, and 3M reflective tongues complete this scrambled iteration.

The Jordan 5 What The released in November of 2020 and retailed for $220.
